The paper focuses on improving the performance of cross-project defect prediction, which is a software engineering problem. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category. The proposed method involves selecting training data based on similarity and the number of defects, which involves machine learning techniques such as feature selection and instance selection. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories. The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed method using AUC values, which is a common evaluation metric in the field of computer security (cs.CR) and system identification (cs.SI).
